.TH LBZFORCE 1
.SH NAME
lbzforce \- force a '.bz2' extension on all lbzip2 files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lbzforce
[ name ...  ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I  lbzforce
forces a .bz2 extension on all
.I lbzip2
files so that
.I lbzip2
will not compress them twice.
This can be useful for files with names truncated after a file transfer.
On systems with a 14 char limitation on file names, the original name
is truncated to make room for the .bz2 suffix. For example,
12345678901234 is renamed to 12345678901.bz2. A file name such as foo.tbz
is left intact.
